      "_comment": "Per-predicate fleet-wide adoption rate. Each row = one predicate name; value = fraction of fleet hosts that satisfy it. Operator sorts to find the gap — e.g. `any_gpu_vram_at_least_80gib` = 0.05 means 5% of fleet has at least one >=80 GiB GPU. Per SDD-993 a SAIN-01 SATISFIES this predicate via its RTX PRO 6000 96 GB primary (Oracle Core); its RTX 5090 32 GB internal secondary + RTX 4090 24 GB OcuLink eGPU do not individually clear 80 GiB but the box does. The threshold stays a fleet-standardisation dial. Lets operator standardise the threshold the fleet REALLY supports.",
